# GraphQL Input Contract Sync

When changing GraphQL mutation/query input contracts, never update only one layer.

- If an input type changes in `apps/api/src/schema/**/*.graphql`, update the matching Zod schema in `packages/validation/src/**/*.ts`.
- Also update every payload builder or caller that sends that input, especially pages like `apps/web/src/pages/ItineraryBuilderPage.tsx`.
- Regenerate web GraphQL types after schema/document changes: `pnpm --filter @tour/web codegen` or the web build script.
- Before finishing, verify the contract with typechecks:
  - `pnpm --filter @tour/api typecheck`
  - `pnpm --filter @tour/validation typecheck`
  - `pnpm --filter @tour/web typecheck`

Checklist for GraphQL input changes:

- [ ] GraphQL SDL updated
- [ ] Zod schema updated
- [ ] Related payload builders/callers updated
- [ ] Web codegen regenerated
- [ ] Typechecks run

Example:

- If `PlanStopNestedInput` adds or removes a field in `apps/api/src/schema/plan.graphql`, also update `packages/validation/src/plan.schema.ts` and the request payloads built in `apps/web/src/pages/ItineraryBuilderPage.tsx`.
